This is a simple javascript that adds a unicode &quot;&quot; to the beginning of html page title.  This can be easily coded using the youtube javascript api.  Just add the following code when the youtube playstate changes to &quot;YT.PlayerState.PLAYING&quot;.<p>The js basically looks like this:
function onPlayerStateChange(event) {
  var player = event.target;
  switch (event.data) {
    case YT.PlayerState.PLAYING:
      document.title = &#x27;&#x27; + document.title;
    break;
  }
}
